ZH: 我要扫地。
EN: I need to sweep the floor.
ZH: 请帮我扫一下屋子。
EN: Please help me clean the room.
ZH: 妈妈喜欢扫地。
EN: Mom enjoys sweeping the floor.
ZH: 我们需要扫除这里的垃圾。
EN: We need to clean up the rubbish here.
ZH: 他打算明天扫院子。
EN: He plans to sweep the yard tomorrow.
ZH: 我每天都要扫地。
EN: I have to sweep the floor every day.
ZH: 在中国，很多人早上起床第一件事就是扫地。
EN: In China, many people's first task in the morning is to sweep the floor.
ZH: 孩子们扫了一整天的地，累坏了。
EN: The children sweep the floor all day and are exhausted.
ZH: 我把所有的书都扫进了垃圾桶。
EN: I swept all the books into the trash can.
ZH: 猫把毛发扫落在了地上。
EN: The cat swept its fur onto the floor.
ZH: 爷爷扫年前。
EN: Grandpa sweeps before the New Year.
ZH: 他用扫帚扫地板。
EN: He sweeps the floor with a broom.
ZH: 妹妹扫去了屋子里的灰尘。
EN: My little sister swept away the dust in the room.
ZH: 我弟弟在扫阳台。
EN: My younger brother is sweeping the balcony.
ZH: 保洁阿姨正在扫大厅。
EN: The cleaning aunt is sweeping the hall.
ZH: 我们在海滩上捡贝壳时，把沙子扫进了海。
EN: When we were picking up seashells on the beach, we swept the sand into the sea.
ZH: 他一边扫地一边唱歌。
EN: He sings while sweeping the floor.
ZH: 她拿着扫把在厨房里扫地。
EN: She is sweeping the kitchen floor with a broom.
ZH: 母亲扫去了家里所有的不干净。
EN: Mother swept away all the dirt in the house.
